Git

Git is a Version Control System (VCS).

It is a software installed on your computer that helps you:

Track code changes
Save different versions of your project
Restore older versions if something breaks
Work on new features using branches
Manage project history
Example

Suppose you're building a Python Flask project.

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Created login feature"

Git stores these changes locally on your computer.

Think of Git as:

📖 A diary that records every change you make to your code.

🔹 GitHub

GitHub is a cloud-based platform that hosts Git repositories online.

It helps you:

Store code on the internet
Backup your projects
Collaborate with other developers
Share projects with recruiters
Contribute to open-source projects
Example

After creating commits with Git:

git push origin main

Your code gets uploaded to GitHub.

Think of GitHub as:

☁️ Google Drive for Git repositories.

